{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1243/comments/3564482.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1243/_/diff#comment-3564482"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1243, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1243.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1243"}}, "title": "Modify Exceptions to print file/line info"}, "content": {"raw": "looks good. \n\nwe try to follow the coding style guide in gazebo - can you break the code into two lines so it's within a max line width 80 chars, e.g.\n\n\n```\n#!c++\n\n  (gazebo::common::Console::err(this->file, this->line)) << \"EXCEPTION: \" \n      << *this << std::endl;\n```\n\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>looks good. </p>\n<p>we try to follow the coding style guide in gazebo - can you break the code into two lines so it's within a max line width 80 chars, e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span>  <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">gazebo</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">common</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Console</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">this</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"k\">this</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">line</span><span class=\"p\">))</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;EXCEPTION: &quot;</span> \n      <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">this</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">endl</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</pre></div>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2014-10-22T18:39:06.338088+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ian Chen", "uuid": "{eaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd}", "li